      • getPartnerInfo

        public static ApiService.PartnerOutput getPartnerInfo(java.lang.String uri)
        Retrieves partner pattern information based on a source URI by making a request to partner app of the API server. Example: URI = "arabidopsis.org" request to API server: https://testapi.arabidopsis.org/partners?sourceUri=arabidopsis.org returns: partnerId = "tair", targetUri = "http://back-prod.arabidopsis.org"
        Parameters:
        uri - URI of client's request
        Returns:
        unique identifier for the partner corresponding to the request URI

      • checkAccess

        public static ApiService.AccessOutput checkAccess(java.lang.String url,
                                  java.lang.String loginKey,
                                  java.lang.String partnerId,
                                  java.lang.String credentialId,
                                  java.lang.String remoteIp)
        Retrieves the access status of the client for a resource request
        Parameters:
        url - resource path that the client tries to access. (e.g: "/news/2015/07/01")
        credentialId - client's party ID if resource that the client tries to access is paid content
        loginKey - client's login key, if login is required to access the resource
        partnerId - unique identifier for the partner that owns the requested resource
        Returns:
        String indicating the access status (OK, NeedSubscription, NeedLogin) or an error message

      • checkMeteringLimit

        public static java.lang.String checkMeteringLimit(java.lang.String ip,
                                  java.lang.String partnerId)
        Retrieves the metering of the client based on the client's IP address.
        Parameters:
        ip - client's IP address.
        Returns:
        String indicating client's metering status. (OK, Warn, Blocked)

      • incrementMeteringCount

        public static java.lang.String incrementMeteringCount(java.lang.String ip,
                                      java.lang.String partnerId)
        Increase metering count associated with the given IP address and partner ID by one.
        Parameters:
        ip - remote IP address
        partnerId - unique identifier for the partner
        Returns:
